{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "HMRC to itemise everything on self-assessment tax payment request",
        "additional_details": "In our view, when HMRC asks self-employed people to pay money, notices should clearly explain what the charge is for, not just include a overall SA BALANCING CHARGE. Detail should set out how it was calculated, which tax year it relates to, and any penalties or interest added. ",
        "background": "We call on the HMRC to set out more details on self-assessment tax payment requests. We think HMRC should explain what it is that a self-employed person owes in detail.",
